                            <AssayComments>The crystal structure of HC63 Fab bound to X-31 BHA complex was solved by molecular replacement. Antibody name and chain isotypes are specified in the paper [PMID: 10944356]. The BHA fragment is composed of the complete mature HA1 and the extracellular domain of HA2. There are two Fab molecules and a trimer of HA1/HA2 chains in the asymmetric unit. HA-binding sites of both Fabs, the first (chains H and L) and the second (chains T and U) are identical and located on HA1 chains A and C for the first Fab, and C and E for the second Fab of two monomers. A third potential Fab binding site on the HA1 chains E and A is free.</AssayComments>
